{
  "stem": "5639.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I have to do it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the situation-- if you want, I can talk about it now, or if you want--",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--I can talk about it in chronological order.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Which way do you want?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were traditional.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- I mean father, mother, and so on-- were traditional.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not particularly observant as far as the lesser holy days.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This is not a description according to Judaism.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "To Judaism there are no lesser holidays, all are equally important.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my mother kept kosher, but I think it was part of a culture, rather than of a belief.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] My parents went to synagogue on Rosh Hashanah and on Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I did it for fun like all teenagers did.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I wasn't forced to do it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I went to a Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a private Jewish school which had a very long name because it had the name of the founder, and the founder were [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it was a Jewish gymnasium in the name of family [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a private school that had all the right of-- here you say-- we said state school.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And here, state school is not a private school, but in Poland, to have the right of state school, means to have the highest rights as any highest educational institution has got.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was very elitist and very selective.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But like most of Jewish institutions, there was always room for charity, and the families who could afford to pay paid in such a way that in fact you paid for another child.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I learned Hebrew from the time zero, from the--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not davening.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We started with Hebrew from grade one, I think, or grade two.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
